{
  "texts": [
    "Through continuous monitoring of various building systems and data analytics, DT can preemptively detect potential problems, consequently reducing maintenance costs and minimizing operational downtime (Khajavi et al. 2019; Hosamo, Imran, et al. 2022).",
    "Furthermore, building engineers are equipped with essential data and knowledge to promptly address issues.",
    "This results in improved system reliability and enhanced occupant experience.",
    "DT in maintenance makes it easy to track the history of building systems, giving engineers access to data that can help identify patterns and optimization opportunities.",
    "A DT of a commercial office building can continuously monitor the HVAC system and detect any abnormal fluctuations in temperature or pressure (Ammar et al. 2022b)."
  ]
}